			<div id="post-3619" class="hentry p2 post publish author-c4chaos category-dharma-practice category-open-practice category-spirituality y2009 m12 d09 h05 alt">
				<h3 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.c4chaos.com/2009/12/why-shinzen-young-is-my-main-dharma-teacher/" title="Permalink to Why Shinzen Young is My Main Dharma Teacher" rel="bookmark">Why Shinzen Young is My Main Dharma Teacher</a></h3>
				<div class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2009-12-10T00:28:36+0000">Thursday, December 10th, 2009</abbr></div>
				<div class="entry-content">
<p>In the beginning of this year, 2009, I&#8217;ve made a connection to a geeky dharma teacher. Since then I&#8217;ve made significant progress in my meditation practice and still going strong. In fact, as a result, I&#8217;ve made meditation as an integral part of my lifestyle. I owe a lot of this to my main dharma [&hellip;]</p>
